The paper proposes a deep learning method for dense prediction tasks, specifically for image segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also focuses on learning the shapes and sizes of patches from data, which involves optimization and learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also proposes a novel architecture for the network, which involves technical solutions for restoring spatial correspondence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. The paper also involves differentiable modules, which can be used for optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for image segmentation, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible category.
